==遺傳學==
2019年發表在《歐洲人類遺傳學雜誌-自然》上的一項最新遺傳研究表明，西亞（阿拉伯人），歐洲人，北非人，南亞人（印度人）和一些中亞人的人口彼此密切相關。他們可以與撒哈拉以南非洲人或東亞人口區分開。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6871633/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-06-01 |archive-date=2020-05-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200529095050/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6871633/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在現代[[遺傳學|遺傳學]][[基因|基因]]研究的最新成果中，一般將[[Y染色体|Y染色体]][[单倍型类群|单倍型类群]][[单倍型类群I_(Y-DNA)|I]]，與自[[末次冰盛期|末次冰盛期]]之前就居於本地的歐洲人相關<ref name=rootsi>{{Citation |doi=10.1086/422196 |last1=Rootsi |first1=S. ''et al.'' |author-separator=, |last2=Magri |author-name-separator= |year=2004 |first2=C |last3=Kivisild |first3=T |last4=Benuzzi |first4=G |last5=Help |first5=H |last6=Bermisheva |first6=M |last7=Kutuev |first7=I |last8=Bara� |first8=L |last9=Perici� |first9=M |displayauthors=9 |title=Phylogeography of Y-Chromosome Haplogroup I Reveals Distinct Domains of Prehistoric Gene Flow in Europe |url=http://www.familytreedna.com/pdf/DNA.RootsiHaplogroupISpread.pdf |journal=American Journal of Human Genetics |volume=75 |issue=1 |pages=128–137 |pmid=15162323 |pmc=1181996 |postscript=. |access-date=2009-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090624135411/http://www.familytreedna.com/pdf/DNA.RootsiHaplogroupISpread.pdf |archive-date=2009-06-24 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>
，其中[[Y染色体|Y染色体]][[单倍型类群|单倍型类群]][[单倍型类群_I1_(Y-DNA)|I1]]與[[北歐|北歐]][[日耳曼人|日耳曼人]]相關<ref name=genographic>[https://genographic.nationalgeographic.com/atlas.html Genographic Project of National Geographic]{{dead link|date=2017年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref><ref name=newphylo>"New Phylogenetic Relationships for Y-chromosome Haplogroup I: Reappraising its Phylogeography and Prehistory," Rethinking the Human Evolution, Mellars P, Boyle K, Bar-Yosef O, Stringer C, Eds. McDonald Institute for Archaeological Research, Cambridge, UK, 2007, pp. 33–42 by Underhill PA, Myres NM, Rootsi S, Chow CT, Lin AA, Otillar RP, King R, Zhivotovsky LA, Balanovsky O, Pshenichnov A, Ritchie KH, Cavalli-Sforza LL, Kivisild T, Villems R, Woodward SR</ref>。
